OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FSixteen months after a landslide
OL,6,Felection victory, the chancellor finds
OL,7,Fherself under constant attack in the
OL,8,Fpress and, if the polls are accurate,
OL,9,Fdeeply unpopular with the public.
OL,11,FIn a recent radio interview on LBC, it
OL,12,Fwas suggested to Rachel Reeves that
OL,13,Fthe honourable thing to do would be to
OL,14,Fdeliver her Budget and immediately
OL,15,Fresign.
OL,17,FLabour was elected promising to raise
OL,18,Ftaxes by #8.5 billion, increase
OL,19,Fspending by #9.5 billion and borrow
OL,20,F#3.5 billion in order to deliver on
OL,21,Fits manifesto.
