OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FIn her first Budget last October, the
OL,6,Fchancellor instead raised taxes by #40
OL,7,Fbillion, spending by #76 billion and
OL,8,Fborrowing by #36 billion.
OL,10,FSaying one thing in opposition and
OL,11,Fdoing something vastly different in
OL,12,Fgovernment is never good for public
OL,13,Ftrust.
OL,15,FReeves argues she had no choice - that
OL,16,Ftough decisions were needed to repair
OL,17,Fpublic services and fix the public
OL,18,Ffinances - but we were told that a
OL,19,Fslate had been "wiped clean".
