OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FAnd she'll point to the havoc caused
OL,6,Fby President Trump's tariffs, which
OL,7,Fhave pushed up borrowing costs for
OL,8,Fgovernments worldwide and reduced tax
OL,9,Frevenues.
OL,11,FThese arguments have merit, and it
OL,12,Fwould be unreasonable to hold Reeves
OL,13,Fresponsible for 15 years of weak
OL,14,Fgrowth in Britain.
OL,16,FBut Labour in government has also
OL,17,Fproved as accident-prone as Paddington
OL,18,FBear - and without the compensatory
OL,19,Fcharm.
