OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FSome of the chancellor's problems have
OL,6,Fbeen self-inflicted. As one of the
OL,7,FBank of England's former chief
OL,8,Feconomists, Andy Haldane, puts it: "it
OL,9,Fhas been a bad hand played, in truth,
OL,10,Fpretty poorly."
OL,12,FMISTAKE 1 - THE TAX LOCK
OL,14,FIn many ways, the original villain of
OL,15,Fthe piece is a Tory.
OL,17,FJeremy Hunt left Rachel Reeves with a
OL,18,Fplan that looked undeliverable.
