OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FIn the months before last year's
OL,6,Felection, when he was chancellor, he
OL,7,Ffunded two cuts to employee National
OL,8,FInsurance (a tax) by pencilling in
OL,9,Fdeep, unspecified cuts to future
OL,10,Fpublic spending. Even at the time, it
OL,11,Flooked like a cynical trap.
OL,13,FThe head of the OBR described the
OL,14,Fpublic finances as "a work of
OL,15,Ffiction". Before the election, a choir
OL,16,Fof experts - the IFS, Resolution
OL,17,FFoundation, Institute for Government
OL,18,Fand the IMF - all warned that the
OL,19,Fnumbers almost certainly didn't add up.
