OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FLabour's original mistake was not to
OL,6,Fagree. Instead, it went along with the
OL,7,Ffiction - and then doubled down by
OL,8,Fpromising not to raise income tax,
OL,9,FNational Insurance or VAT in its
OL,10,Fmanifesto.
OL,12,FEconomists warned this was an unwise
OL,13,Fpromise for a chancellor to make.
OL,15,FAttempting to stick to the manifesto
OL,16,F"tax-lock" has shaped and warped some
OL,17,Fof the big decisions Reeves has made
OL,18,Fsince.
OL,20,FMISTAKE 2 - WELFARE CUTS
