OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FThe resulting Universal Credit and
OL,6,FPersonal Independence Payments Bill
OL,7,Fwas so harsh and so poorly designed
OL,8,Fthat it looked doomed instantly.
OL,10,FLabour MPs revolted. The government U-
OL,11,Fturned - first on Winter Fuel
OL,12,FPayments, then on tightening PIP
OL,13,Feligibility.
OL,15,FThe welfare misjudgments have made the
OL,16,Fgovernment appear weak and inept, and
OL,17,Fleft the chancellor out of pocket,
OL,18,Fhaving banked savings she then failed
OL,19,Fto secure.
