OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FWhen chancellors present a Budget,
OL,6,Fthey always leave some money unspent
OL,7,Fas "headroom" - a financial buffer to
OL,8,Fprotect against future storms that
OL,9,Fcould blow plans off course.
OL,11,FIn her first Budget, Reeves left
OL,12,Fherself just #10 billion against her
OL,13,Fmain fiscal rule: that the Current
OL,14,FBudget must be in balance by 2029`30.
OL,15,FThat's around a third of the average
OL,16,Fbuffer chancellors have kept since
OL,17,F2010.
