OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,F#10 billion was not enough to absorb
OL,6,Freally bad news. And now the OBR is
OL,7,Fset to downgrade its forecast for
OL,8,Ftrend productivity growth, blowing
OL,9,Fstraight through it.
OL,11,FThe timing of the downgrade is
OL,12,Fgenuinely bad luck - but it was always
OL,13,Fa risk. The OBR has been more
OL,14,Foptimistic than almost every other
OL,15,Feconomic forecaster for several years.
OL,17,FReeves could have spent less and
OL,18,Fcreated more headroom in her first
OL,19,FBudget. She chose not to. The gamble
OL,20,Fhas backfired.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/21
