OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FMISTAKE 4 - THE WRONG TAX RISE
OL,7,FThe chancellor wants to improve public
OL,8,Fservices and invest in infrastructure
OL,9,Fto revive economic growth. Higher
OL,10,Ftaxes are necessary to fund these
OL,11,Fgoals.
OL,13,FBut last October she raised employer
OL,14,FNational Insurance and, crucially,
OL,15,Flowered the earnings threshold at
OL,16,Fwhich it kicks in. These changes
OL,17,Fcombined raise #25 billion but, in
OL,18,Fpractice, around a third of that has
OL,19,Fbeen lost through lower wages,
OL,20,Fsqueezed company profits, fewer jobs
OL,21,Fand higher welfare bills.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
