OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FThere is now convincing evidence that
OL,6,Fthe lower threshold, combined with a
OL,7,Fsteep rise in the minimum wage, has
OL,8,Fdestroyed part-time and entry-level
OL,9,Fjobs, pushed up inflation, made public
OL,10,Fservices more expensive to deliver,
OL,11,Fand angered many businesses.
OL,13,FReeves had other options. Reversing
OL,14,FHunt's NI cuts or raising income tax
OL,15,Fwould likely have been less
OL,16,Feconomically damaging, but doing
OL,17,Feither would have been a clear breach
OL,18,Fof the manifesto "tax lock" promise.
