OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FThe UK's national debt is near post-
OL,6,Fwar highs. Growth prospects are
OL,7,Fanaemic. Government borrowing costs
OL,8,Fare the highest in the G7. Investors
OL,9,Fcurrently see the UK as a riskier bet
OL,10,Fthan France - a country with higher
OL,11,Fdebt levels and a politically
OL,12,Fparalysed government.
OL,14,FReeves needs to increase taxes but
OL,15,Fwants to boost growth, cut inflation
OL,16,Fand give the Bank of England room to
OL,17,Freduce interest rates at the same time.
OL,19,FThe objectives are commendable, but
OL,20,Fpreparation for this Budget has been
OL,21,Fchaotic, bordering on shambolic.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/21
