OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FThree months of constant speculation
OL,6,Fabout which taxes will go up has
OL,7,Fsuffocated spending and investment.
OL,8,FHouseholds and businesses are sitting
OL,9,Fon their hands - and that means lost
OL,10,FGDP, lower national income and reduced
OL,11,Fwell-being.
OL,13,FWe have been marched up the hill,
OL,14,Fapparently in preparation for income
OL,15,Ftax increases and then marched
OL,16,Fstraight back down again.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/21
