OL,3,CHow the Chancellor misplayed a bad hand
OL,5,FThe risks of this approach are
OL,6,Fobvious. A comparatively small group
OL,7,Fof losers will shout loudly; the
OL,8,Fwinners probably won't care. And in
OL,9,Fthe scramble to raise a billion here
OL,10,Fand a billion there, something could
OL,11,Fblow up - remember the Pasty Tax under
OL,12,FGeorge Osborne?
OL,14,FIt all feels a bit like muddling on at
OL,15,Fa moment that demands boldness.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/21
